# DEBUG_LOG discipline

This project follows the [debug-log-skill](https://github.com/<you>/debug-log-skill) protocol. Before writing any non-trivial code, and after fixing any bug, obey the rules below.

## Before coding

1. Open `DEBUG_LOG.md` at the project root. Skim titles. Read any entry whose prevention rule touches the file(s) you are about to edit.
2. Read the relevant `references/<track>.md` from the skill folder for the track(s) this project uses, plus `references/cross-cutting.md` (always applicable).
3. For new features, also work through `references/preempt-checklist.md` and `references/pre-mortem-workflow.md`.
4. State a plan before changes: goal, files touched, interfaces preserved, prevention rules that apply, verification approach.

## Tracks in this project

Edit the checkbox list to reflect this project's stack. Delete rows that don't apply.

- [ ] web — React / Next.js / TypeScript / Node
- [ ] ios — Swift / SwiftUI / UIKit
- [ ] android — Kotlin / Compose
- [ ] macos — Swift / AppKit
