- [ ] swift — language-level
- [x] cross-cutting — always on

## The four non-negotiable rules

1. **Sequence.** Entries are numbered `DL-001`, `DL-002`, … Never skip. Never reuse.
2. **Never skip.** Every bug fix gets a `DL-NNN` entry in the same commit as the fix. No silent fixes.
3. **Read before coding.** See above.
4. **Append-only.** Never edit or delete an entry. Supersede with a new one that cross-references the old.

## After fixing a bug

1. Append a `DL-NNN` entry to `DEBUG_LOG.md` with the seven-field template.
2. Write the prevention rule as imperative, specific, and checkable. End with a **Why:** one-liner.
3. Stage `DEBUG_LOG.md` in the same commit as the fix.
4. If the same rule appears in three entries, promote it to `PREVENTION_RULES.md`.

## Entry template

```markdown
### DL-XXX — [Short Title]

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| **Date** | YYYY-MM-DD |
| **Severity** | Build Error / Runtime Crash / ANR / Logic Bug / Flaky Test / Warning-as-Error / Perf Regression / Incident |
| **Track** | web / ios / android / macos / kotlin / swift / cross-cutting |
| **File(s)** | `path/to/file.ext` |
| **Symptom** | What failed. Quote the error message. |
| **Root Cause** | Why. 1–3 sentences. Name the misconception. |
| **Fix** | What was changed. Commit SHA if available. |
| **Prevention Rule** | Imperative, specific, checkable. **Why:** one-liner. |
```
